<div class="container place" style="background-color:#bbdefb;border-radius:5px;padding:40px;">
    <h3 class="place" style="color:darkcyan;font-family:Quicksand;">What is our relationship to the SDGS?</h3>
    &nbsp;
    <div class="place">
        <img style="width:200px;height:200px;" src="~/Media/Images/sdg.png" />
    </div>
    &nbsp;
    <p style="font-size:small;font-family:'Segoe UI';">
        Our organization focuses on marine life which is in line with the SDG 14, Life Below Water.
        The <a style="text-decoration-line:none;" href="https://sdgs.un.org/goals">Sustainable Development Goals (SDGS)</a> are goals set by the Division of Sustainable Development Goals (DSDG). It is a set of goals that are set to be met to maintain the correct developments in contries.
        These development must be in line with these goal to create an acceptable environment for all living creatures.
        The goals were designed to be blueprints to achieve a better and more sustainable future for all. They address global challenge and urge the global population to acknowledge them when developing their infrastruture.
        The Division sets up agenda for periods of time. These agenda are excuted throughout the year and report is written up to have record of the progress. Here available is the <a style="text-decoration-line:none;" href=" https://sustainabledevelopment.un.org/content/documents/21252030%20Agenda%20for%20Sustainable%20Development%20web.pdf">2023 Agenda</a>
        and the <a style="text-decoration-line:none;" href=" https://unstats.un.org/sdgs/report/2021/The-Sustainable-Development-Goals-Report-2021.pdf">2021 Report</a>.
        For more information, see their website linked in the full name above. For more information on our main goal, visit <a style="text-decoration-line:none;" href="https://www.un.org/sustainabledevelopment/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/14+Why-it-Matters-2020.pdf">SDG 14 Life Below Water</a>.
    </p>
</div>
