<div class="container place" style="padding: 40px;">
    <h3 class="place" style="color:darkcyan;font-family:Quicksand;">What do we stand for?</h3>
    &nbsp;
    &nbsp;
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm-4" >
            <img style="width:100px; height:100px;" src="~/Media/Images/protect.png" />
            <h6>Preservation and Protection</h6>
            <p style="font-size:small;font-family:'Segoe UI';">
                We look to preserving marine life, especially endangered species that are being poached and inadvertedly dying due to pollution in our waters.
                We protect these animals by making sure their area of living is known and that people acknowledge that they are in a specific territory.
                Not only are we protecting animals, we are also protecting people. Some sea and fresh water creatures are dangerous. Therefore, people have to know
                that a specific area in water or a specific body of water is inhabited by these animals.
            </p>&nbsp;
        </div>
        <br />
        <div class="col-sm-4">
            <img style="width:100px; height:100px;" src="~/Media/Images/nurture.png" />
            <h6>Livelihood and Nurturance</h6>
            <p style="font-size:small;font-family:'Segoe UI';">
                We aim to make marine life happy. Most animals in this case love attention and care from humans, as long as they do not feel that they pose a threat towards them and their territory.
                In doing this, we keep them entertained and also sharpen their perspectives of human interactions. We want them to feel safe around our oceans. We employ scuba divers in our foundation
                who have experience and know how to safely interact with the beings. We apply kindness and nurturance to our ojectives because we do not know what these creature have been through,
                so we in turn must show them love and care in every manner we can when interacting with them.
            </p>&nbsp;
        </div>
        <br />
        <div class="col-sm-4">
            <img style="width:100px; height:100px;" src="~/Media/Images/save.png" />
            <h6>Safety and Security</h6>
            <p style="font-size:small;font-family:'Segoe UI';">
                One of the most unfortunate curcumstances that effect marine life badly is pollution. We try our uttermost best to decrease pollution in the ocean and offer stafety and security to our animals.
                One aspect that makes matters hard is poaching in our oceans. We have patrol systems that work on checking for any disturbances within the ecosystem and its animals.
                Food security is another concept that we tackle for these creatures, to make sure that thye consume food that is not contaminated by pollution, especially with the problem of plastic waste that is consistantly increasing
                and harming animals in water. All in all, we advocate for the safety and security of these animals under circumstances that they cannot protect themselves against.

            </p>&nbsp;
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
